[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi folks, I have a requirement where I need to transfer the ownership of a <code>CString</code> to C code, but I found that implementing <code>ForeignOwnable</code> for <code>CString</code> is quite difficult.</p>\n<p>I want <code>into_foreign</code> to return a C <code>char *</code>, but if we only have a C <code>char *</code>, then <code>from_foreign</code> doesn’t have enough information to take back the <code>CString</code>.</p>\n<p><code>CString</code> is based on <code>KVec</code> and requires the pointer, length, and capacity in order to take back the <code>CString</code>. How should I handle this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ForeignOwnable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CString</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PointedTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">ffi</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">c_char</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Borrowed</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">BorrowedMut</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">into_foreign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PointedTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// Returns a c_char *</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">from_foreign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PointedTo</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// Converts a c_char * back to a Rust-owned CString</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 521403287,
        "sender_full_name": "JCKeep",
        "timestamp": 1748663004
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In <code>into_foreign</code> we could make the allocation fit exactly to the length of the string and then in <code>from_foreign</code> we search for the nul byte</p>",
        "id": 521412189,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748670834
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What if we do not fit the length, just ignore <code>buf[len..capacity]</code> in <code>from_foreign</code>, it work well with current <code>CString</code>. If we fit the allocation length in <code>into_foreign</code>, it cost a little due to realloc.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">into_foreign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PointedTo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">buf</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">into_raw_parts</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">from_foreign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PointedTo</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">strlen</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// capacity &gt;= len, just ignore `buf[len..capacity]`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">CString</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">buf</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KVec</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from_raw_parts</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 521415076,
        "sender_full_name": "JCKeep",
        "timestamp": 1748674019
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>free</code> and <code>realloc</code> need to know the current size of the allocation</p>",
        "id": 521419157,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748676674
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/ForeignOwnable.20for.20CString/near/521419157\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>free</code> and <code>realloc</code> need to know the current size of the allocation</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, but in this case, I think the behavior is predictable and correct. we <code>drop</code> it have two step:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>call <code>drop_in_place</code> in range <code>buf[..len]</code>,  <em>It's fine, we restore the len</em></li>\n<li>call <code>free</code> on <code>buf[..len]</code>, <em>and it's fine too, realloc will free <code>buf[..capacity]</code></em></li>\n</ol>\n<p>So even if we ignore <code>buf[len..capacity]</code>, it will be freed correctly. But it's dangerous. <span aria-label=\"eyes\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f440\" role=\"img\" title=\"eyes\">:eyes:</span></p>",
        "id": 521421487,
        "sender_full_name": "JCKeep",
        "timestamp": 1748679060
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't understand your argument why it's fine.</p>",
        "id": 521421577,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748679125
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am also not following. Do you perhaps mean to change how the <code>Allocator</code> trait works (i.e. the requirements of e.g. <code>free</code>)?  Or perhaps modifying how <code>CString</code> (or <code>KVec</code>) allocate etc. internally instead?</p>\n<p>What <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"546447\">@Benno Lossin</span> is trying to say is that currently, if you don't change anything, then e.g. what you pass to <code>free</code> is a <code>Layout</code>, not just a pointer, and that the pointer passed needs to be one that was previously returned by the allocator and so on.</p>",
        "id": 521428444,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748685505
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Edited -- I misread <code>..len</code>, so the first part didn't make sense, sorry.</p>",
        "id": 521428638,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748685697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Even if you have <code>into_foreign</code> shrink the allocation or otherwise make it work, you also have to call <code>strlen</code> in <code>from_foreign</code>, but that method is suppose to be cheap.</p>",
        "id": 521429955,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1748686956
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/ForeignOwnable.20for.20CString/near/521429955\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Even if you have <code>into_foreign</code> shrink the allocation or otherwise make it work, you also have to call <code>strlen</code> in <code>from_foreign</code>, but that method is suppose to be cheap.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Oh right, the performance overhead is too high. It’s difficult to implement <code>ForeignOwnable</code> for <code>CString</code> with zero cost.</p>\n<p>I had an idea — embedding the length at the beginning of the string might reduce the overhead.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//   +--------------------+-----------------------+------------+</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//   |  length            |   character data      |   '\\0'     |</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//   +--------------------+-----------------------+------------+</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">//                         ^</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 521431310,
        "sender_full_name": "JCKeep",
        "timestamp": 1748688174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sounds like <code>ThinBox</code></p>",
        "id": 521433018,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748689758
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But even if you have the length, i.e. no need to find the <code>\\0</code>, you still need something that allows you to free it or a <code>realloc</code> that requires less.</p>",
        "id": 521433258,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748689983
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could keep both the length and the capacity behind, I guess :)</p>",
        "id": 521433387,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748690125
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Storing length and capacity behind the pointer would work.</p>",
        "id": 521434567,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1748691136
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But maybe that should be a new type? Not sure ...</p>",
        "id": 521434581,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1748691157
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, my feeling is that we would probably want to have another type/name for that, especially since <code>CString</code> is well-known in the stdlib (and C developers wouldn't expect that anyway)</p>",
        "id": 521434992,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748691542
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is also worth considering whether your specific use case requires it to be mutable after creation.</p>",
        "id": 521435703,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1748692113
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/ForeignOwnable.20for.20CString/near/521434581\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But maybe that should be a new type? Not sure ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>yeah think so too.</p>",
        "id": 521436014,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748692410
    }
]